This is the best! I've made it a dozen times and it's always appreciated by the diners. Substitute Red Wine Vinegar for the Sherry and you end up with a nice Sweet and Sour taste. If you like it spicy, you'll need to add either more chili-garlic sauce or other types of chilis. I used fresh tuna and served it over egg noodles the last time and everyone was delighted.

