Mine turned out a lot better than I expected it to. I had no fresh ginger, so I used some pickled ginger instead. I also added some of the juice from the pickled ginger in too. I will definitely keep making it like that, I am going to start making this all the time. The flavor was intense and everyone loved it. I added broccoli and green beans because that is what I had in the fridge, but I agree any vegetable will work. This sauce would be great over salmon, with chicken, even just veggies. I am going to experiment with lime, marinating the shrimps or chicken longer, and baking the sauce over fish.

